human rights watch (hrw) is an american-founded international non-governmental organization that conducts research and advocacy on human rights. hrw headquarters are in new york city with offices in amsterdam, beirut, berlin, brussels, chicago, geneva, johannesburg, london, los angeles, moscow, nairobi, paris, san francisco, sydney, tokyo, toronto, washington, d.c., and zurich. the organization's annual expenses totaled $50.6 million in 2011 and $69.2 million in 2014.